  "body": "<!-- Briefly describe the issue you're experiencing. Tell us what you were trying to do and what happened instead. -->\r\n\r\n\"using ShortStrings for *;\" in contracts/utils/cryptography/EIP712.sol breaks brownie compiler, furthermore, there is a solidity issue https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/11882 that discourages this pattern which will eventually be removed.\r\n\r\n**üíª Environment**\r\n\r\nBrownie v1.19.3, MacOS\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n\r\nBrownie compiler does not support `using ... for *` wildcard syntax (see issue https://github.com/eth-brownie/brownie/issues/1266), furthermore this pattern is discouraged and will eventually be removed, see https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/11882\r\n\r\n",
