    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @jhiver and thanks for raising that issue.\r\n\r\nWhile this syntax may be removed, it is currently valid solidity. So I would argue that this is a bug on the brownie side and not in our contract. \r\n\r\nWe usually preferred doing `using xxx for *` than having multiple entries for the same library and different types ... but at some point we considered removing the `using` syntax completely. We will discuss this in light of this possible removal (that would be breaking, so I don't see that happening before solidity 0.9.0)",
